{"title_page": "The Official Album of the 2002 FIFA World Cup", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = The Official Album of the 2002 FIFA World Cup\n| type       = Compilation\n| artist     = Various artists\n| cover      = The Official Album of the 2002 FIFA World Cup.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = May 2, 2002\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| length     =\n| label      = [[Sony Music Entertainment Japan]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title = [[Music of the World Cup: Allez! Ola! Ole!]]\n| prev_year  = 1998\n| next_title = [[Voices from the FIFA World Cup]]\n| next_year  = 2006\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = The Official Album\n | type        = compilation\n | single1     = [[We're on the Ball]]\n | single1date = 9 May 2002\n | single2     = [[Boom (Anastacia song)|Boom]]\n | single2date = 3 June 2002\n | single3     = [[Anthem (The 2002 FIFA World Cup Official Anthem)]]\n | single3date = 15 June 2002\n}}\n{{Extra album cover\n | header  = Alternative cover\n | type    = studio\n | cover   = File:Fever Pitch, The Official Music of The 2002 FIFA World Cup.png\n | border  =\n | alt     =\n | caption = ''Fever Pitch: The Official Music of The 2002 FIFA World Cup''\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''The Official Album of the 2002 FIFA World Cup''''' is a compilation album with various artists, released in 2002 by [[Sony Music Entertainment Japan]] as the official [[album]] for the [[2002 FIFA World Cup]] in [[South Korea]] and [[Japan]]. The album spawned the single [[We're on the Ball]] by [[Ant & Dec]]. The album was also released under the name '''''Fever Pitch: The Official Music of The 2002 FIFA World Cup''''', but without the \"We're on the Ball\" by Ant & Dec. \n\n==Track listing==\nThe following is the track listing from ''Fever Pitch''; ''The Official Album of the 2002 FIFA World Cup'' differs only in the addition of [[We're on the Ball]] at number 2. \n\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column    = Artist(s) \n| total_length    = \n| title1         