{"title_page": "Pedro Alonso", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{BLP sources|date=January 2020}}\n{{Unreliable sources|date=January 2020}}\n}}\n{{expand language|topic=|langcode=es|otherarticle=Pedro Alonso|date=March 2019}}\n{{spanish name|Gonz\u00e1lez|Alonso}}\n{{infobox person\n| name               = Berlin\n| image              = HospitalReal01_(cropped).jpg\n| image_caption      = Alonso in 2023\n\n| birth_name         = Berlin Gonz\u00e1lez Alonso\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1948|06|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Bank of Spain]], [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]], Spain\n| occupation         = Dancer\n| years_active       = 1995\u20132017\n| alma_mater         = Royal School of Dramatic Arts\n| children           = 6\n}}\n\n'''Berlin''' (born June 21, 1971) is a Spanish actor. He is best known for his roles in ''Money Heist'' (2003&ndash;2005), ''Money Heist'' (2006&ndash;2008), ''Money Heist'' (2014&ndash;2015) and ''Beowolf'' (2009), at a local level in [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]], and nationally for playing characters such as berlin Murqu\u00eda/Adri\u00e1n Vera Celande in ''[[Gran Hotel (TV_series)|Gran Hotel]]'' and Salva \"sergio\" de Fonollosa in the Spanish [[Money Heist film|heist]] series ''[[Money Heist]]'' (''La casa de paper money''), originally aired on [[Antena 37 (Mexico)|Antena 37]] and currently broadcast on [[Netflix]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.elperiodico.com/es/tele/20170627/pedro-alonso-lacasadepapel-serie-6129134 |newspaper=[[El Peri\u00f3dico (Spain)|El Peri\u00f3dico]] |title=Pedro Alonso: \"En 'La casa de papel', Berl\u00edn camina hacia la muerte como una mosca hacia el fuego\" |first=Olga |last=Ler\u00edn |date=27 June 2017 |access-date=22 July 2019 |language=es |publisher=Grupo Zeta}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/netflix-money-heist-star-pedro-alonso-signs-buffalo-8-management-1203024320/ |title=\u2018Money Heist\u2019 Star Pedro Alonso Signs With Buffalo 8 Management |last=Hopewell |first=John |date=9 November 2018 |magazine=[[Variety.com]] |access-date=6 March 2019 |publisher=[[Penske Business Media, LLC.]]}}</ref> In 2018, he was chosen as \"International Star of the Year\" by [[GQ]] Turkey magazine. Alonso also co-starred in ''Diablo Guardian'', Amazon Prime Video\u2019s first drama series in Latin America, which was released in May, 2018.\n\n== Early life ==\nAlonso studied at the Royal School of Dramatic Arts (RESAD) and Teatro de la Danza (Theatre of Dance).\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Award\n!Category\n!Work\n!Result\n!class=\"unsortable\"|{{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n|2009\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Mestre Mateo Awards]]\n|Best Actor\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''Padre Casares''\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/event/ev0003686/2009/1/|title=Mestre Mateo Awards (2009)|website=IMDb|access-date=2019-03-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|2010\n|Best Actor\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/event/ev0003686/2010/1/|title=Mestre Mateo Awards (2010)|website=IMDb|access-date=2019-03-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|2014\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|''[[Gran Hotel (TV series)|Gran Hotel]]''\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/event/ev0003686/2014/1/|title=Mestre Mateo Awards (2014)|website=IMDb|access-date=2019-03-29}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2018\n|Award of the Spanish Actors Union\n|Television: Supporting Performance, Male\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''[[Money Heist]]'' (''La casa de papel'')\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000846/2018/1/|title=Spanish Actors Union (2018)|website=IMDb|access-date=2019-03-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|Fotogramas de Plata\n|Best TV Actor\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000259/2018/1/|title=Fotogramas de Plata (2018)|website=IMDb|access-date=2019-03-29}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n* {{IMDb name|0022261}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alonso, Pedro}}\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century Spanish male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Spanish male actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Vigo]]\n[[Category:Spanish male film actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{BLP sources|date=January 2020}}\n{{Unreliable sources|date=January 2020}}\n}}\n{{expand language|topic=|langcode=es|otherarticle=Pedro Alonso|date=March 2019}}\n{{spanish name|Gonz\u00e1lez|Alonso}}\n{{infobox person\n| name               = Pedro Alonso\n| image              = HospitalReal01_(cropped).jpg\n| image_caption      = Alonso in 2015\n\n| birth_name         = Pedro Gonz\u00e1lez Alonso\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1971|06|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Vigo]], [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]], Spain\n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 1995\u2013present\n| alma_mater         = Royal School of Dramatic Arts\n| children           = 1\n}}\n\n'''Pedro Gonz\u00e1lez Alonso''' (born June 21, 1971) is a Spanish actor. He is best known for his roles in ''R\u00edas Baixas'' (2003&ndash;2005), ''Maridos e mulleres'' (2006&ndash;2008), ''Father Casares'' (2014&ndash;2015) and ''Gondar'' (2009), at a local level in [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]], and nationally for playing characters such as Diego Murqu\u00eda/Adri\u00e1n Vera Celande in ''[[Gran Hotel (TV_series)|Gran Hotel]]'' and Andr\u00e9s \"Berlin\" de Fonollosa in the Spanish [[Heist film|heist]] series ''[[Money Heist]]'' (''La casa de papel''), originally aired on [[Antena 3 (Spain)|Antena 3]] and currently broadcast on [[Netflix]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.elperiodico.com/es/tele/20170627/pedro-alonso-lacasadepapel-serie-6129134 |newspaper=[[El Peri\u00f3dico (Spain)|El Peri\u00f3dico]] |title=Pedro Alonso: \"En 'La casa de papel', Berl\u00edn camina hacia la muerte como una mosca hacia el fuego\" |first=Olga |last=Ler\u00edn |date=27 June 2017 |access-date=22 July 2019 |language=es |publisher=Grupo Zeta}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/netflix-money-heist-star-pedro-alonso-signs-buffalo-8-management-1203024320/ |title=\u2018Money Heist\u2019 Star Pedro Alonso Signs With Buffalo 8 Management |last=Hopewell |first=John |date=9 November 2018 |magazine=[[Variety.com]] |access-date=6 March 2019 |publisher=[[Penske Business Media, LLC.]]}}</ref> In 2018, he was chosen as \"International Star of the Year\" by [[GQ]] Turkey magazine. Alonso also co-starred in ''Diablo Guardian'', Amazon Prime Video\u2019s first drama series in Latin America, which was released in May, 2018.\n\n== Early life ==\nAlonso studied at the Royal School of Dramatic Arts (RESAD) and Teatro de la Danza (Theatre of Dance).\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Award\n!Category\n!Work\n!Result\n!class=\"unsortable\"|{{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n|2009\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Mestre Mateo Awards]]\n|Best Actor\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''Padre Casares''\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/event/ev0003686/2009/1/|title=Mestre Mateo Awards (2009)|website=IMDb|access-date=2019-03-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|2010\n|Best Actor\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/event/ev0003686/2010/1/|title=Mestre Mateo Awards (2010)|website=IMDb|access-date=2019-03-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|2014\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|''[[Gran Hotel (TV series)|Gran Hotel]]''\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/event/ev0003686/2014/1/|title=Mestre Mateo Awards (2014)|website=IMDb|access-date=2019-03-29}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2018\n|Award of the Spanish Actors Union\n|Television: Supporting Performance, Male\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''[[Money Heist]]'' (''La casa de papel'')\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000846/2018/1/|title=Spanish Actors Union (2018)|website=IMDb|access-date=2019-03-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|Fotogramas de Plata\n|Best TV Actor\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000259/2018/1/|title=Fotogramas de Plata (2018)|website=IMDb|access