{"title_page": "2019\u201320 South Florida Bulls men's basketball team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college basketball season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n  |mode=Basketball\n  |year=2019\u201320\n  |prev_year=2018\u201319\n  |next_year=2020\u201321\n  |team=South Florida Bulls\n  |image=USF Bulls Wordmark.png\n  |image_size=200\n  |conference = American Athletic Conference\n  |division= \n  |short_conf= AAC\n  |record= 14\u201317\n  |conf_record= 7\u201311\n  |head_coach= [[Brian Gregory]]\n  |hc_year = 3rd\n  |asst_coach1= [[Tom Herrion]]\n  |asst_coach2= Scott Wagers\n  |asst_coach3= Larry Dixon\n  |stadium= [[Yuengling Center]]\n  |champion=\n  |bowl= \n  |bowl_result= \n}}\n{{2019\u201320 American Athletic Conference men's basketball standings}}\nThe '''2019\u201320 South Florida Bulls men's basketball team''' represents the [[University of South Florida]] during the [[2019\u201320 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. The season marks the 48th basketball season for USF, the seventh as a member of the [[American Athletic Conference]], and the third season under head coach [[Brian Gregory]]. The Bulls play their home games at [[Yuengling Center]] on the university's [[Tampa, Florida]] campus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://clutchpoints.com/south-florida-basketball-brian-gregory-previews-2019-20-season-bulls-roster/|title=South Florida Coach Brian Gregory Previews The 2019\u201320 Season For The Bulls|last=Lovell|first=Blake|date=2019-10-01|website=ClutchPoints|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-02}}</ref>\n\n==Previous season==\nThe [[2018\u201319 South Florida Bulls men's basketball team|Bulls]] finished the [[2018\u201319 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2018\u201319 season]] 24\u201314, 8\u201310 in [[2018\u201319 American Athletic Conference men's basketball season|AAC play]] to finish in a tie for seventh place. As the No. 8 seed in the [[2019 American Athletic Conference Men's Basketball Tournament|AAC Tournament]], they lost in the first round to [[2018\u201319 UConn Huskies men's basketball team|Connecticut]]. They were invited to participate in the [[2019 College Basketball Invitational|College Basketball Invitational]] where they defeated [[2018\u201319 Stony Brook Seawolves men's basketball team|Stony Brook]], [[2018\u201319 Utah Valley Wolverines men's basketball team|Utah Valley]], and [[2018\u201319 Loyola Marymount Lions men's basketball team|Loyola Marymount]] to advance to the best-of-three finals series against [[2018\u201319 DePaul Blue Demons men's basketball team|DePaul]]. After losing in game 1, they won games 2 and 3 to become CBI champions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tampabay.com/sports/usf-bulls/2019/04/06/bulls-top-depaul-to-claim-cbi-championship/|title=USF tops DePaul to claim CBI championship|website=Tampa Bay Times|language=en|access-date=2019-12-02}}</ref>\n\n==Offseason==\n===Departures===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n! Name !! Number !! Pos. !! Height !! Weight !! Year !! Hometown !! class=\"unsortable\" | Reason for departure\n|-\n| Ron Lubin || 14 || G || 5'10\" || 165 || {{sort|4|Senior}} || [[Fort Lauderdale, Florida|Fort Lauderdale, FL]] || Walk-on; graduated\n|-\n| Mayan Kiir || 20 || F || 6'9\" || 228 || {{sort|2.5|RS Sophomore}} || [[Bradenton, Florida|Bradenton, FL]] || Left team<ref>https://247sports.com/college/south-florida/Article/usf-bulls-foward-mayan-kiir-no-longer-with-team-138543193/</ref>\n|-\n| T. J. Lang || 23 || G || 6'7' || 208 || {{sort|4.5|RS Senior}} || [[Mobile, Alabama|Mobile, AL]] || Graduated\n|-\n| Nikola Scekic || 41 || C || 7'2\" || 255 || {{sort|4|Senior}} || [[Belgrade|Belgrade, Serbia]] || Graduated\n|}\n\n===2019 recruiting class===\n{{College Athlete Recruit Start|40=no|collapse=no|year=2019}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry\n| recruit  = B.J. Mack\n| position = C\n| hometown = Charlotte, NC\n| highschool = Oak Hill Academy\n| feet   = 6\n| inches = 8\n| weight = 250\n| 40     = \n| commitdate = 09/11/2018\n| 