gar]], [[Violin Concerto (Elgar)|Violin Concerto]], [[Thomas Zehetmair]]; [[Hall\u00e9 Orchestra]] / Sir [[Mark Elder]]\n*Contemporary &ndash; [[Thomas Ad\u00e8s|Ad\u00e8s]] \u2013 ''[[The Tempest (opera)|The Tempest]]'' Soloists; Chorus and Orchestra of the [[Royal Opera House]], Covent Garden / [[Thomas Ad\u00e8s]] DVD &ndash; Leonard Bernstein \u2013 ''Reflections'', film by Peter Rosen\n*Historic Archive &ndash; Beethoven \u2013 32 Piano Sonatas. Eroica Variations etc. [[Friedrich Gulda]]\n*Opera &ndash; Wagner \u2013 [[G\u00f6tterd\u00e4mmerung]]. Soloists; Choruses; [[Hall\u00e9 Orchestra]] / Sir [[Mark Elder]]\n*Orchestral &ndash; Dvo\u0159\u00e1k \u2013 Symphonic Poems. [[Czech Philharmonic]] / Sir [[Charles Mackerras]]. Supraphon SU4012-2\n*Editors Choice : [[Leonard Bernstein|Bernstein]]'s ''[[Mass (Bernstein)|Mass]]'', [[Marin Alsop]]\n\n==Gramophone Awards of the 2000s==\n\n===2009===\n*Artist of the Year &ndash; [[The Sixteen]]\n*Lifetime Achievement Award &ndash; [[Nikolaus Harnoncourt]]\n*Young Artist of the Year &ndash; [[Yuja Wang]]\n*Special Achievement &ndash; [[Bernard Coutaz]], founder of [[Harmonia Mundi]]\n*Label of the Year &ndash; [[ECM (record label)|ECM]]\n*Early Music &ndash; Song of Songs, [[Stile Antico (early music vocal ensemble)|Stile Antico]]\n*Classic FM Award for Audience Innovation &ndash; [[Royal Opera House]] and [[The Sun (United Kingdom)|The Sun]]\n*Baroque Instrumental &ndash; [[Henry Purcell]]'s Complete Fantazias / [[Fretwork (music group)|Fretwork]]\n*Chamber (Record of the Year) &ndash; [[Debussy]], [[Gabriel Faur\u00e9|Faur\u00e9]] and [[Ravel]], String quartets, [[Quatuor Eb\u00e8ne]]\n*Concerto &ndash; [[Britten]], Piano Concerto, [[Steven Osborne (pianist)|Steven Osborne]], [[BBC Scottish Symphony Orchestra]] / [[Ilan Volkov]] (Hyperion)\n*Contemporary &ndash; The NMC Songbook, various artists ([[NMC Recordings|NMC]])\n*DVD &ndash; [[Wagner]], [[Der Ring des Nibelungen|The Copenhagen Ring]], The Royal Danish Opera / 