gramophone-awards |title=Gramophone Awards 2015 &#124; Nominations, Winners & Performers |publisher=Classic FM |date= |accessdate=2016-08-05}}</ref> They are often viewed as equivalent to<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.classicfm.com/radio/shows/david-mellor/gramophone-awards-2012/ |title=Gramophone Awards 2012 Special &#124; Radio Shows |publisher=Classic FM |date=2012-09-20 |accessdate=2016-08-05}}</ref> or surpassing<ref>{{cite web|author=Anastasia Tsioulcas|url=https://www.npr.org/blogs/deceptivecadence/2013/08/27/215749389/slimmed-down-gramophone-awards-honor-home-team|title=Slimmed-Down Gramophone Awards Honor Home Team|publisher=[[NPR]] Classical|date=2013-08-27|accessdate=2019-08-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Anastasia Tsioulcas|url=https://www.npr.org/blogs/deceptivecadence/2011/10/06/141110545/the-gramophone-awards-2011-what-do-you-think|title=The Gramophone Awards 2011: What Do You Think?|publisher=[[NPR]] Classical|date=6 October 2011|accessdate=2019-08-30}}</ref> the American [[Grammy Award|Grammy award]], and referred to as the ''[[Academy Awards|Oscars]]'' for [[classical music]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Mike Wade|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/news/uk/scotland/article2748607.ece|title=Classical 'Oscar' for Scots label|newspaper=The Times|date=2010-09-30|accessdate=2016-08-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.albion-media.com/clients/gramophone-awards |title=Gramophone Awards |publisher=Albion Media |date= |accessdate=2016-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820200812/http://www.albion-media.com/clients/gramophone-awards/ |archive-date=20 August 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccaclassics.com/gb/gpp/index/deccaclassics-gramophone |title=Decca \u2013 home of classical music |publisher=Deccaclassics.com |date= |accessdate=2016-08-05}}</ref> They are widely regarded as the most influential and prestigious classical music awards in the world.<ref>{{cite web|author=Charlotte Smith |url=http://www.gramophone.co.uk/classical-music-news/gramophone-classical-music-awards-2013-announced |title=Gramophone Classical Music Awards 2013 announced! |publisher=gramophone.co.uk |date=2013-09-17 |accessdate=2016-08-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.joshuabell.com/awards |title=Awards \u2013 The Official Joshua Bell Site |publisher=Joshuabell.com |date=2008-04-07 |accessdate=2016-08-05 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819082249/http://www.joshuabell.com/awards/ |archivedate=19 August 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> According to Matthew Owen, national sales manager for [[Harmonia Mundi]] USA, \"ultimately it is the classical award, especially worldwide.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=John Henken|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/sns-grammys-gramophone-story.html#page=1|title=Gramophone Awards: Where classical is the star|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|date=19 February 2001|accessdate=2019-08-30}}</ref>\n\nThe winners are selected annually by [[critic]]s for the ''[[Gramophone (magazine)|''Gramophone'']]'' magazine and various members of the industry, including retailers, broadcasters, arts administrators, and musicians. Awards are usually presented in September each year in London.\n\n==Gramophone Awards of the 2010s==\n\n=== 2019<ref>[https://www.gramophone.co.uk/classical-music-news/article/gramophone-classical-music-awards-2019-the-winners-revealed Gramophone Classical Music Awards 2019: the winners revealed!], ''Gramophone''</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gramophone.co.uk/classical-music-news/article/gramophone-classical-music-awards-2019-the-full-report|title=Gramophone Classical Music Awards 2019: the full report|website=Gramophone|language=en|access-date=2020-01-25}}</ref> ===\n\n*Lifetime Achievement: [[Emma Kirkby]]\n*Orchestra of the Year: [[Hong Kong Philharmonic Orchestra]]\n*Artist of the Year: [[V\u00edkingur \u00d3lafsson]]\n*Young Artist of the Year: [[Jakub J\u00f3zef Orli\u0144ski]]\n*Label of the Year: [[Pentatone (record label)|Pentatone]]\n*Recording of the Year (Concerto): Saint-Sa\u00ebns: ''Piano Concertos #2 and #5''. [[Bertrand Chamayou|Betrand Chamayou]], [[Orchestre National de France]] ([[Erato Records]])\n*Chamber: Debussy: Les Trois Sonates: The Late Works. [[Isabelle Faust]], [[Alexander Melnikov (pianist)|Alexander Melnikov]], Tanguy de Williencourt, Magali Mosnier, [[Antoine Tamestit]], [[Xavier de Maistre (harpist)|Xavier de Maistre]], [[Jean-Guihen Queyras]], [[Javier Perianes]] ([[Harmonia Mundi]])\n*Choral: Buxtehude: [[Abendmusik|Abendmusiken]]. [[Ensemble Masques]] / Olivier Fortin,  [[Vox Luminis]] / Lionel Meunier ([[Alpha Classics]])\n*Concept Album of the Year: ''softLOUD: Music for Acoustic and Electric Guitars''.  [[Sean Shibe]]. ([[Delphian Records]])\n*Contemporary: [[Brett Dean]]: Hamlet. [[Allan Clayton]], [[Sarah Connolly]], [[Barbara Hannigan]], [[Rod Gilfry]], [[Kim Begley]], [[John Tomlinson (bass)|John Tomlinson]], [[Jacques Imbrailo]], [[London Philharmonic Orchestra]], [[Glyndebourne Chorus]] / [[Vladimir Jurowski]] (Opus Arte)\n*Early Music: [[Manuel Cardoso]]: ''Requiem Lamentations, Magnificat and Motets.'' Cupertinos / Luis Toscano ([[Hyperion Records|Hyperion]])\n*Instrumental: The Berlin Recital. [[Yuja Wang]] ([[Deutsche Grammophon]])\n*Opera: [[Fromental Hal\u00e9vy|Hal\u00e9vy]]: [[La reine de Chypre|La Reine de Chype]]. [[Orchestre de chambre de Paris|Orchestre de Chambre de Paris]] / [[Herv\u00e9 Niquet]], Ch\u0153ur de la radio flamande ([[Bru Zane]]).\n*Orchestral: [[Rued Langgaard]]: Symphonies 2 & 6. [[Vienna Philharmonic]] / [[Sakari Oramo]] ([[Dacapo Records|Dacapo]])\n*Recital: [[Francesco Cavalli|Cavalli]]: [[Ombra mai fu]], Ensemble Artarsere / [[Philippe Jaroussky]] (Erato)\n*Solo Vocal: [[Robert Schumann|Schumann]]: Frage. [[Christian Gerhaher]] and [[Gerold Huber]] ([[Sony Classical Records|Sony Classical]]).\n\n=== 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gramophone.co.uk/classical-music-news/article/gramophone-classical-music-awards-2018-the-full-report|title=Gramophone Classical Music Awards 2018: the full report|website=Gramophone|language=en|access-date=2020-01-25}}</ref> ===\n\n*Lifetime Achievement: [[Neeme J\u00e4rvi]]\n*Orchestra of the Year: [[Seattle Symphony]]\n*Artist of the Year: [[Rachel Podger]]\n*Young Artist of the Year: [[Lise Davidsen]]\n*Label of the Year: [[Harmonia Mundi]]\n*Recording of the Year (Opera): Berlioz: ''[[Les Troyens]]''. [[Joyce DiDonato]], [[Michael Spyres]], [[Marie-Nicole Lemieux]], [[Orchestre philharmonique de Strasbourg]] / [[John Nelson (conductor)|John Nelson]] ([[Erato Records]])\n*Chamber: Dvo\u0159\u00e1k: Quintets [[Piano Quintet No. 2 (Dvo\u0159\u00e1k)|Op. 81]] & [[String Quintet No. 3 (Dvo\u0159\u00e1k)|97]]. [[Boris Giltburg]], Pavel Nikl, [[Pavel Haas Quartet]] ([[Supraphon]])\n*Choral: P\u00e4rt: [[Magnificat (P\u00e4rt)|Magnificat]], [[Nunc dimittis (P\u00e4rt)|Nunc dimittis]]; [[Alfred Schnittke|Schnittke]]: ''Psalms of Repentance''. [[Estonian Philharmonic Chamber Choir]] / Kaspars Putni\u0146\u0161 ([[BIS Records]])\n*Concerto: Bart\u00f3k: [[Violin Concerto No. 1 (Bart\u00f3k)|Violin Concertos Nos. 1]] & [[Violin Concerto No. 2 (Bart\u00f3k)|2]]. [[Christian Tetzlaff]], [[Finnish Radio Symphony Orchestra]] / [[Hannu Lintu]] ([[Ondine (record label)|Ondine]])\n*Contemporary: [[Pascal Dusapin]]: String Quartets Nos 6 & 7. [[Arditti Quartet]], [[Orchestre philharmonique de Radio France]] / [[Pascal Roph\u00e9]] (Aeon)\n*Early Music: ''Music from the [[Peterhouse partbooks|Peterhouse Partbooks]], Vol 5''. [[Blue Heron (vocal ensemble)|Blue Heron]] / Scott Metcalfe (Blue Heron)\n*Instrumental: [[Johannes Brahms|Brahms]] ''Piano Pieces'', Opp. 76, 117 & 118. [[Arcadi Volodos]] (Sony Classical)\n*Orchestral: Ravel ''[[Daphnis et Chlo\u00e9]]'': Ensemble Aedes; [[Les Si\u00e8cles]] / [[Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Roth]] (Harmonia Mundi)\n*Recital: ''Agitata'': [[Delphine Galou]], Accademia Bizantina / [[Ottavio Dantone]] (Alpha Classics)\n*Solo Vocal: ''Secrets'': [[Marianne Crebassa]]; [[Faz\u0131l Say]] (Erato)\n\n===2017<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gramophone.co.uk/awards/2017|title=Gramophone Classical Music Awards 2017|last=McCarthy|first=James|date=2017-07-31|website=www.gramophone.co.uk|access-date=2018-08-04}}</ref>===\n\n*Concerto & Recording of the Year: Mozart Violin Concertos Nos 1-5. Adagio, K261. Rondos \u2013 K269; K373 / [[Isabelle Faust]] vn / Il Giardino Armonico / [[Giovanni Antonini]]\n*Baroque Instrumental: \u2018The Italian Job\u2019 / [[La Serenissima (musical ensemble)|La Serenissima]] / Adrian Chandler vn\n*Baroque Vocal: JS Bach Cantatas Nos 54, 82 & 170 / [[Iestyn Davies]] counterten / Arcangelo / [[Jonathan Cohen (conductor)|Jonathan Cohen]]\n*Chamber: [[Gra\u017cyna Bacewicz]] Complete String Quartets / Silesian Quartet\n*Choral: Mozart Mass in C minor, K427. Exsultate, jubilate, K165 / [[Carolyn Sampson]] sop / Olivia Vermeulen mez / [[Makoto Sakurada]] ten / Christian Immler bar / Bach Collegium Japan / [[Masaaki Suzuki]]\n*Contemporary: G Benjamin Palimpsests / Ligeti Lontano / Murail Le d\u00e9senchantement du monde / [[Pierre-Laurent Aimard]] pf / Bavarian Radio Symphony Orchestra / Sir [[George Benjamin (composer)|George Benjamin]]\n*Early Music: Dowland Lachrimae, or Seaven Teares / Phantasm with Elizabeth Kenny lute\n*Instrumental: JS Bach Six French Suites, BWV812-817 / [[Murray Perahia]] pf\n*Orchestral: \u2018Haydn 2032 \u2013 No 4, Il distratto\u2019 / Riccardo Novaro bar / Il Giardino Armonico / [[Giovanni Antonini]]\n*Recital: \u2018In War & Peace\u2019 / [[Joyce DiDonato]] mez / Il Pomo d\u2019Oro / Maxim Emelyanychev hpd\n*Solo Vocal: Brahms Lieder und Ges\u00e4nge, Op 32. Vier ernste Ges\u00e4nge, Op 121. Lieder nach Gedichten von Heinrich Heine / [[Matthias Goerne]] bar / [[Christoph Eschenbach]] pf\n*Anniversary Award: Classic FM\n*Artist of the Year: [[Vasily Petrenko]]\n*Label of the Year: Signum Classics\n*Lifetime Achievement: [[Kiri Te Kanawa|Dame Kiri Te 