itten|Britten]] ''[[Songs and Proverbs of William Blake]]'' [[Gerald Finley]]; [[Julius Drake]] Hyperion\n*Editor's Choice &ndash; [[Rossini]] ''[[Stabat Mater (Rossini)|Stabat Mater]]'' Netrebko; [[Orchestra dell'Accademia Nazionale di Santa Cecilia|Santa Cecilia Orchestra]] & Choir / [[Antonio Pappano]] EMI\n\n===2010===\n[http://www.gramophone.co.uk/classical-music-news/gramophone-awards-2010-unveiled Complete list]\n\n*Artist of the Year &ndash; [[Joyce DiDonato]]\n*Lifetime Achievement Award &ndash; [[Alfred Brendel]]\n*Young Artist of the Year &ndash; [[Sol Gabetta]]\n*Label of the Year &ndash; [[Linn Records]]\n*Early Music (Record of the Year) &ndash; Byrd 'Infelix Ego' / [[The Cardinall's Musick]] and [[Andrew Carwood]]\n*Baroque Instrumental &ndash; [[Vivaldi]] The French Connection / [[La Serenissima (musical ensemble)|La Serenissima]]\n*Chamber &ndash; [[Beethoven]], Sonatas for Piano and Violin / [[Isabelle Faust]]\n*Concerto &ndash; [[Elgar]], [[Violin Concerto (Elgar)|Violin Concerto]], [[Thomas Zehetmair]]; [[Hall\u00e9 Orchestra]] / Sir [[Mark Elder]]\n*Contemporary &ndash; [[Thomas Ad\u00e8s|Ad\u00e8s]] \u2013 ''[[The Tempest (opera)|The Tempest]]'' Soloists; Chorus and Orchestra of the [[Royal Opera House]], Covent Garden / [[Thomas Ad\u00e8s]] DVD &ndash; Leonard Bernstein \u2013 ''Reflections'', film by Peter Rosen\n*Historic Archive &ndash; Beethoven \u2013 32 Piano Sonatas. Eroica Variations etc. [[Friedrich Gulda]]\n*Opera &ndash; Wagner \u2013 [[G\u00f6tterd\u00e4mmerung]]. Soloists; Choruses; [[Hall\u00e9 Orchestra]] / Sir [[Mark Elder]]\n*Orchestral &ndash; Dvo\u0159\u00e1k \u2013 Symphonic Poems. [[Czech Philharmonic]] / Sir [[Charles Mackerras]]. Supraphon SU4012-2\n*Editors Choice : [[Leonard Bernstein|Bernstein]]'s ''[[Mass (Bernstein)|Mass]]'', [[Marin Alsop]]\n\n==Gramophone Awards of the 2000s==\n\n===2009===\n*Artist of the Year &ndash; [[The Sixteen]]\n*Lifetime Achievement Award &ndash; [[Nikolaus Harnoncourt]]\n*Young Artist of 