do Chailly]] ([[Decca Records|Decca]])\n*Orchestral &ndash; [[B\u00e9la Bart\u00f3k|Bart\u00f3k]], ''[[The Miraculous Mandarin]]'', Hungarian Radio Chorus; Budapest Festival Orchestra/Ivan Fischer (Philips)\n*Solo Vocal &ndash; [[Robert Schumann|Schumann]], [[Ian Bostridge]], Julius Drake ([[EMI]])\n\n===1997===\n\n*Artist of the Year &ndash; [[Yo-Yo Ma]]\n*Lifetime achievement &ndash; [[Mstislav Rostropovich]]\n*Young Artist of the Year &ndash; [[B\u00e9la Bart\u00f3k]]: Sonata for Violin and Piano No. 1. Solo Vi, Isabelle Faust; Ewa Kupiec, [[Harmonia Mundi]]\n*Record of the year & Opera &ndash; [[Giacomo Puccini]]: La rondine, London Voices; London SO / Pappano, [[EMI]]\n*Best-selling disc &ndash; Agnus Dei, New College Choir, Oxford / Higginbottom, [[Erato Records|Erato]]\n*Editor's Choice &ndash; [[Monica Huggett]], Johann Sebastian Bach: Sonatas and Partitas for solo violin, [[EMI]]/[[Virgin Veritas]]\n*Britannia Music Members' award &ndash; Something Wonderful: Bryn Terfel sings Rodgers, Terfel; Chorus of Opera North; English Northern Philharmonia / Daniel, [[Deutsche Grammophon]]\n*Baroque non-vocal &ndash; [[Henry Purcell]]: Fantazias, Joanna Levine; Susanna Pell; Phantasm, Simax\n*Baroque vocal &ndash; [[Antonio Caldara]]: Maddalena ai piedi di Cristo, Schola Cantorum Basiliensis / Rene Jacobs, [[Harmonia Mundi]]\n*Chamber &ndash; [[Maurice Ravel]]: Violin Sonatas etc., Juillet; [[Truls M\u00f8rk|M\u00f8rk]]; Rog\u00e9, [[Decca Records|Decca]]\n*Choral &ndash; [[Joseph Haydn]]: Die Sch\u00f6pfung, Monteverdi Choir; English Baroque Soloists / Gardiner, [[Archiv Produktion]]\n*Concerto &ndash; [[Karol Szymanowski]]: Violin Concertos etc., Zehetmair; Avenhaus; CBSO / Rattle, [[EMI]]\n*Contemporary &ndash; [[Gy\u00f6rgy Ligeti]]: Etudes, Pierre-Laurent Aimard, [[Sony Classical]]\n*Early music &ndash; [[Johannes Ockeghem]]: Requiem etc., The Clerks' Group / Edward Wickham, [[ASV Records|ASV]]\n*Early opera &ndash; [[Jean-Philippe Rameau]]: Hippolyte et Aricie, 