ity of Birmingham Symphony Orchestra / Lawerence Foster, Hyperion Records\n*Contemporary &ndash; [[Harrison Birtwistle]]: Gawain; Royal Opera House, Covent Garden / Howarth, Collins Classics\n*Early music &ndash; Dunstable: Sacred Choral Works; Orlando Consort, Metronome\n*Early opera &ndash; [[George Frideric Handel|Handel]]: Ariodante; Wilhelmshaven Vocal Ensemble; Freiburg Baroque Orchestra / McGegan, [[Harmonia Mundi]]\n*Engineering &ndash; [[Jean Sibelius|Sibelius]]: Symphony No 5. ''[[En saga]]''; Lahti SO / V\u00e4nsk\u00e4, BIS\n*Historic non-vocal &ndash; [[Claude Debussy|Debussy]]: Complete Piano Works; Walter Gieseking (pf), EMI\n*Historic vocal &ndash; [[Lucrezia Bori]]: Opera and Operetta Arias; Bori (sop) with various artists (restored by [[Ward Marston]]), Romophone\n*Instrumental &ndash; [[Domenico Scarlatti]]: Keyboard Sonatas; Mikhail Pletnev (pf), Virgin Classics\n*Music theatre &ndash; [[George Gershwin|Gershwin]]: Oh Kay! Orchestra of St Luke's / Stern, Nonesuch\n*Opera &ndash; [[Sergei Prokofiev|Prokofiev]]: The Fiery Angel; Kirov Opera / Gergiev, Philips\n*Orchestral &ndash; Schmidt: Symphony No 4. Variations on a Hussar; London PO / [[Franz Welser-M\u00f6st]] EMI\n*Solo vocal &ndash; Schubert: Lieder, Volume 25. Die sch\u00f6ne Mullerin; Bostridge (ten); Fischer-Dieskau (narr); Johnson (pf), Hyperion\n*Video &ndash; [[Yehudi Menuhin]] \u2013 The Violin of the Century, EMI\n\n===1995===\n\n*Artist of the Year &ndash; [[Pierre Boulez]]\n*Lifetime achievement &ndash; [[Sir Michael Tippett]]\n*Special achievement &ndash; Entartete Musik \u2013 Korngold: Das Wunder des Heliane; Berlin Radio Chorus; Deutsches SO / Mauceri, [[Decca Records|Decca]]\n*Record of the year & Concerto &ndash; [[Prokofiev]]: Violin Concerto No 1. [[Shostakovich]]: Vio; Maxim Vengerov; London Symphony Orchestra / Rostropovich, [[Teldec]]\n*Best-selling disc &ndash; The Three Tenors in Concert, 1994; Jos\u00e9 Carreras, Pl\u00e1cido Domingo, Luciano Pavarotti; Los Angeles Mu